cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with user-assisted relaying in cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses stochastic geometry to analyze the performance of the relaying scheme. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes two geometric cooperation policies for the relaying scheme. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper evaluates the transmission rate performance of the relaying scheme. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to user-assisted relaying.
